Gaze facial authentication profile

This profile configures PAM to use Gaze (pam_gaze.so) for facial
authentication. Users who have enrolled their face can authenticate
without entering a password; others fall through to standard password
authentication automatically.

REQUIREMENTS
- gazed.service must be running (systemctl enable --now gazed)
- pam_gaze.so must be installed at /usr/lib/security/pam_gaze.so
- Users must enroll their face: gaze add-face <username> <face-name>

USAGE
  authselect select custom/gaze [features...]
  authselect select custom/gaze with-faillock
  authselect select custom/gaze with-fingerprint with-faillock

OPTIONAL FEATURES
  with-faillock     Track failed authentication attempts with pam_faillock
  with-fingerprint  Enable fingerprint authentication as an additional fallback
  with-mkhomedir    Automatically create home directories on first login
